<div class="row">
	<div class="twelvecol">
	  <h1 class="home"><span class="logo">gKnome</span>
		<span class="tagline">Whole Genome Sequencing Analysis Pipeline</span></h1>
    <h2>Analysis Scenarios</h2>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
	<div class="eightcol">
    <p>gKnome pipeline analyzes data from Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS) or Whole Exome Sequencing (WES) experiments in one of four scenarios: 1) case vs. control, 2) case only with common, rare or unknown diseases, 3) family study and 4) healthy individual. The analysis modules and variant filtering criteria are configured differently to best fit each scenario.</p>
    <p>gKnome provides summary reports at <%= link_to "genome", genome_path(1) %>, <%= link_to "gene", genes_path %>, and <%= link_to "disease", diseases_path %>/<%= link_to "biological process", processes_path %> levels.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="fourcol last">
	  <button class="pipeline">Case / Control</button>
	  <button class="pipeline">Case only</button>
	  <button class="pipeline">Family study</button>
	  <button class="pipeline">Healthy</button>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
	<div class="twelvecol">
    <h2>Overview of Workflow</h2>
    <p>The analysis pipeline is consisted of 3 major modules designed to filter variants based on allele frequency and functional impact, and to enable knowledge enrichment for diseases and pathways.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
	<div class="fourcol">
	  <h3>1. Allele Frequency</h3>
	  <ul class="modules">
      <li>Ethnicity<br>(EUR, AFR, ASN)</li>
	    <li>dbSNP132</li>
	    <li>1000 genomes</li>
	    <li>200 exomes</li>
	    <li>69 &times; CGI genomes</li>
	    <li>De novo mutations</li>
	  </ul>
	</div>
	<div class="fourcol">
	  <h3>2. Functional Impact</h3>
	  <ul class="modules">
      <li>Protein Coding genes (RefSeq, CCDS, ENSEMBL, UCSC Genes)</li>
      <li>Non-coding (miRNA, TFBS)</li>
      <li>Functtional impact prediction<br>(PPH2, SIFT, CONDEL)</li>
	    <li>Sequence Conservations<br>(GERP, PhyloP)</li>
	    <li>Repeated Sequences</li>
	  </ul>
	</div>
	<div class="fourcol last">
	  <h3>3. Knowledge Enrichment</h3>
	  <ul class="modules">
      <li><p>Disease Association<br>(PharmGKB, HuGE, Medvane Genes, SafeGene, HGMD)</p></li>
	    <li><p>Pathways<br>(Gene Ontology, KEGG, BioCarta)</p></li>
	    <li><p>Biological Processes<br>(Gene Ontology)</p></li>
	  </ul>
	</div>
</div>
